document_data.History:
In [[1491 DR]], [[Gundren Rockseeker]], a [[dwarf]] explorer, struck a deal to transfer a wagon full of goods from [[Neverwinter]] to Barthen's store. He hired a group of novice [[adventurer]]s to transport the goods, however he himself was waylaid by [[goblin]] bandits and never made it to the trading post.

During this time, Barthen's Provisions also struck deals to sell dry goods and supplies to [[Tibor Wester's loggers' camp|logging operations]] run by [[Tibor Wester]], the half-brother of Townmaster [[Harbin Wester]], as well as deals to sell herds of [[giant goat]]s on behalf of [[Dagult Neverember]] in order to fund rebuilding efforts in [[Leilon]].

The company went out of business in late [[1495 DR]] or early [[1496 DR]]. About five months later, the building was purchased by an unknown person who donated it to the worship of [[Waukeen]], and it was quickly renovated into the [[Temple of the Coinmaiden]] by [[Ditch Fundi]].{{AI-time}}
